article.headline: Toledo 62, Ball St. 60
article.story: MUNCIE, Ind. (AP) -- Justin Ingram scored nine points, grabbed 13 rebounds and made the game-winning layup at the buzzer to lead Toledo past Ball State 62-60 in the Mid-American Conference opener for both teams Saturday. Ingram scored seven of his nine points in the second half, including a 3-pointer that gave the Rockets (5-8, 1-0 MAC) a one-point lead with 53 seconds remaining. Keonta Howell had 16 points and Kashif Payne added 10 points and five assists for Toledo. Anthony Newell led Ball State (4-10, 0-1) with 11 points and seven rebounds in the Cardinals' fourth straight loss. Peyton Stovall scored seven first-half points as Ball State led 29-22 at halftime. Toledo shot 13-of-23 (57 percent) in the second half and held Ball State to 10-of-29 (35 percent) shooting. The Rockets held a 43-31 rebounding edge and outscored the Cardinals in the paint 27-22.
